\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 50. V. macedonicum} Kosanin & Murb.,{\i  Bull. Inst. Jard. Bot. Univ. Beograd }{\b 1}: 220 (1930). Densely and persistently white-tomentose biennial; stem 100-150 cm. Basal leaves 8-20 × 4-8 cm, elliptical, crenate; petiole 4-9 cm. Cauline leaves decurrent. Inflorescence usually simple. Bracts c. 8 mm, linear-lanceolate, persistently tomentose at least beneath; pedicels almost completely adnate to axis of inflorescence. Calyx 9-11 mm; lobes linear-lanceolate. Corolla c. 25 mm in diameter. Stamens 5; anthers all reniform; filament-hairs white. {\i Calcareous rocks in a river-gorge. Makedonija} ({\i near Poloski Monaskir}). Ju.
\par

