\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 51. V. botuliforme} Murb., {\i Lunds Univ. Årsskr.} nov. ser., {\b 29}({\b 2}): 288 (1933). Like {\b 50} but larger, with compact, less densely tomentose inflorescence; bracts broadly ovate, cuspidate; calyx 5-7 mm; lobes broadly ovate, shortly cuspidate.{\i • N. Greece.} Gr.
\par

