\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 52. V. dentifolium} Delile,{\i  Sem. Hort. Bot. Monsp. }28 (1837) ({\i V. granatense} Boiss.). Persistently greyish-tomentose biennial; stem 100-160 cm. Basal leaves 22-45 × 6-12 cm, oblong-oblanceolate, entire, crenate or dentate, petiolate. Inflorescence freely branched. Bracts 5-7 mm, ovate to deltate, cuspidate; longer pedicels 3-5 mm. Calyx 4-6 mm; lobes ovate-lanceolate. Corolla 22-28 mm in diameter. Stamens 5; anthers all reniform; filament-hairs violet, at least in part. Capsule 5-6 mm, subglobose.{\i  S. Spain} ({\i Sierra Nevada and adjoining region}). Hs. ({\i N.W. Africa.})
\par

