\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 53. V. speciosum} Schrader, {\i Hort. Gotting.} 22 (1809). Persistently tomentose biennial; stem 50-200 cm. Basal leaves 12-40 × 3-14 cm, oblong-oblanceolate to obovate, entire, shortly petiolate. Inflorescence freely branched. Bracts (5-)8-15 (-20) mm, the lower ovate-lanceolate, the upper lanceolate; longer pedicels (3-)5-12 mm. Calyx 3-6 mm; lobes narrowly lanceolate. Corolla 18-30 mm in diameter. Stamens 5; anthers all reniform; filament-hairs white. Capsule 3-7 mm, ovoid-oblong.{\i  S.E. & E.C. Europe, northwards to S.C. Czechoslovakia and westwards to Slovenija.} Al Au Bu Cz Gr Hu Ju ?Po Rm Rs (W) Tu.
